The Treasury said sales of EE U.S.savings bonds were 17 pct higher during March at 703 mln dlrsthan in March, 1986.    It was the highest savings bond sales total for any Marchsince 1978.    Total holdings of U.S. savings bonds reached 94.76 billiondlrs, the highest in the history of the program, the Treasurysaid.    March redemptions fell six pct to 441 mln dlrs last monthfrom 468 mln dlrs in March, 1986.    For the first six months of fiscal 1987, savings bondssales have risen 129 pct from the comparable fiscal 1986 periodto 7.01 billion dlrs from 3.07 billion dlrs, the Treasury said. Reuter&#3;